    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#caillou2010"/>, p. <citedRange>182</citedRange> (mention)</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>60.1831</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>118300</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="Νικίας">Νικία</name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty locus="name" match=".."/></gap>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Offrande de</supplied> Nikias <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Offering of</supplied> Nikias <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Offerta di</supplied> Nikias <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty match=".." locus="name"/></gap>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>As the fragment is broken just after the last letter read here, it is not clear whether a final letter should be restored, producing the nominative case,
                   perhaps followed by other words. However a genitive of 'ownership' of the dedicant is quite plausible (see <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr118400</ref>).</p>
                <p>Like the latter, this vase was found in the fill below the altar bearing <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr114000</ref>. It is thus in clear relation with it.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
